Memory Protection Devices Inc said itexpects to close the previously announced acquisition of theassets and liabilities of Bogen, a division of &lt;Lear SieglerInc>, on April one.    Memory Protection Devices said it received a senior loancommitment letter as well as the requisite waiver under the NewJersey Environmental Control Reclamation Act, both of which arenecessary to complete the acquisition. It declined to providefurther details. Reuter&#3;